title: SIGINT Officer
name: Sailor Hasting
description: Supervise, direct, and provide guidance and technical expertise on all aspects of the employment of SIGINT, systems and personnel in support of tactical, strategic, and national level SIGINT/EW missions. Oversee the management, collection, processing, analysis, and reporting of SIGINT and Electronic Warfare Support (ES) derived intelligence and information.

title: Systems Integration Management Officer
name: Sailor Hasting
description: Oversaw the fielding and training of all SIGINT equipment as well as ensured the unit’s equipment and training requirements were focused in order to meet the collection, processing, and dissemination needs to support both garrison operations as well as operations in the Al Anbar province of Iraq. Additionally I was charged with representing the commanding officer in matters dealing with the coordination of doctrinal development of SIGINT programs of record and service level training development and served as the liaison with Marine Corps Systems Command and other external agencies in order to procure needed systems, training and maintenance.

title: Weapons and Tactics Instructor
name: Sailor Hasting
description: Served as the lead SIGINT instructor for the Marine Corps’ Weapons and Tactics Instructor Course. This course is a graduate level school designed to train instructors in all aspects of aviation weapons and tactics. While serving as lead instructor I provided instruction to over 1600 multi-service and multi-national students and was responsible for the coordination and employment of all national and tactical SIGINT assets as well as the integration and demonstration of emerging SIGINT technologies.
